history.content:
I am currently trying to enroll in CS70 but it gives me a missing discussion error, any way to get around this? 

Also, when I try to enroll for CS160 it tells me that I don't meet the requirements and that seats are reserved, who are they reserved for? (I am an EECS major)

The errors I receive are as followed:

CS70: Error: A Required Related Class (component DIS) must also be Selected. There is an additional component required for enrollment that is missing.

CS160: 

Error: You are unable to enroll in this class at this time. Available seats are reserved and you do not meet the reserve capacity requirements. If a wait list is available, you may still be placed on the waitlist for this class. To do this, select Add Another Class to return to step 1. Select the class link, select the wait list option and resubmit your request.
history.subject: Having trouble enrolling in CS70 and CS160
